IF by istake you commited venv folder and not able to push :

1. Delete existing git history

Inside your project folder run:

rm -rf .git

This removes ONLY git history, not your project files.

2. Create .gitignore

Create .gitignore file with:

venv/
tfenv/
__pycache__/
.ipynb_checkpoints/
*.pyc
.DS_Store
3. Reinitialize git
git init
4. Add remote again
git remote add origin git@github.com:NidhiSah88/ANN_CLASSIFICATION_CHURN_KRISHNAIK.git
5. Add files
git add .

Check what is being added:

git status

Make sure:

venv/ is NOT listed
tfenv/ is NOT listed
6. Commit
git commit -m "Initial commit"
7. Push
git branch -M main
git push -u origin main --force

This will fix the GitHub large file error completely.


