//// KERNEL IS CRASHED ////
FIX:
The logs clearly show the problem:

VS Code is STILL using:

venv/bin/python (Python 3.12)

instead of:

tfenv/bin/python (Python 3.10)

That is why TensorFlow crashes.

The important line is:

Kernel 'venv (Python 3.12.0)' died

and:

Starting Kernel ... venv/bin/python

So the fix is to completely remove the broken venv kernel and force VS Code to use tfenv.

Do this EXACTLY

1. Delete old broken kernel

Run in terminal:

jupyter kernelspec list

You will see kernels like:

venv
tfenv

Now remove broken venv kernel:

jupyter kernelspec uninstall venv

Type y.

2. Re-register tfenv correctly

Activate tfenv:
source tfenv/bin/activate

Then run:

python -m ipykernel install --user --name=tfenv --display-name "TensorFlow Env"
3. Close VS Code completely
Cmd + Q
4. Reopen project

Open ONLY:

ANN_CLASSIFICATION_APP_UDEMY_KRISHNAIK

5. Open notebook

Open:

experiments.ipynb
6. VERY IMPORTANT — select correct kernel

Top-right → click kernel name.

Choose:

Select Another Kernel

Then choose:

TensorFlow Env

NOT:

venv
base
Python 3.12
7. Verify before importing tensorflow

Run this FIRST:

import sys
print(sys.executable)

You MUST see:

.../tfenv/bin/python

If you see venv/bin/python, stop — wrong kernel selected.

8. Then run TensorFlow
import tensorflow as tf
print(tf.__version__)

This should work now without crashing.



