i want to deleete tfenv, and use venv

That’s fine, but your current venv is broken because it uses Python 3.12, which is causing TensorFlow kernel crashes on your Apple Silicon Mac.

The clean solution is:

delete both old environments
recreate venv using Python 3.10
install TensorFlow correctly

use only one environment (venv)
Step 1 — Delete old environments

From project folder:

rm -rf venv
rm -rf tfenv
Step 2 — Create fresh venv with Python 3.10
python3.10 -m venv venv
Step 3 — Activate it
source venv/bin/activate

Now terminal should show:

(venv)
Step 4 — Install packages

For your Apple Silicon Mac:

pip install tensorflow-macos==2.16.2 tensorflow-metal
pip install pandas scikit-learn notebook ipykernel
Step 5 — Register kernel
python -m ipykernel install --user --name=venv --display-name "venv"

Step 6 — Remove old kernels
jupyter kernelspec uninstall tfenv

Type y.

Then optionally:

jupyter kernelspec uninstall venv

if old broken one still exists.

Then re-register again:

python -m ipykernel install --user --name=venv --display-name "venv"

Step 7 — Restart VS Code

Open notebook → select kernel:

venv
Step 8 — Verify

Run FIRST:

import sys
print(sys.executable)

You should see:

.../venv/bin/python

Then test TensorFlow:

import tensorflow as tf
print(tf.__version__)

This should work without crashes now.







