FIXX:

streamlit is running from your Anaconda base Python 3.12 environment, not from your venv.

That’s why it cannot find TensorFlow.

Your error shows:

/opt/anaconda3/lib/python3.12/

which means Streamlit is using conda base.

You must run Streamlit from your venv.

Step 1 — Activate venv

In terminal:

source venv/bin/activate


Your prompt should look like:

(venv)

NOT (base).

If (base) appears, run:

conda deactivate

until only (venv) remains.

Step 2 — Install streamlit inside venv

Run:

pip install streamlit
Step 3 — Verify correct Python

Run:

which python

You should see:

.../ANN_CLASSIFICATION_APP_UDEMY_KRISHNAIK/venv/bin/python

Then:

which streamlit

You should see:

.../ANN_CLASSIFICATION_APP_UDEMY_KRISHNAIK/venv/bin/streamlit
Step 4 — Run app

Now run:

streamlit run app.py

TensorFlow should load correctly now.


