ModuleNotFoundError: No module named 'tensorflow'

You are still running Streamlit from Anaconda base, not from your venv.

The proof is this line:

/opt/anaconda3/lib/python3.12/site-packages/streamlit/

Even though terminal shows (venv), the streamlit command itself is coming from Anaconda.

Fix it like this.

Step 1 — Fully deactivate conda base

Run:

conda deactivate

Keep running it until (base) disappears.

You want:

(venv)

ONLY.

Step 2 — Verify streamlit path

Run:

which streamlit

RIGHT NOW it probably shows:

/opt/anaconda3/bin/streamlit

which is wrong.

Step 3 — Install streamlit inside venv

While only (venv) is active:

pip install streamlit
Step 4 — Verify again

Run:

which streamlit

NOW it should show something like:

.../ANN_CLASSIFICATION_APP_UDEMY_KRISHNAIK/venv/bin/streamlit
Step 5 — Run app correctly

Use:

python -m streamlit run app.py

instead of plain streamlit run app.py.

This forces Streamlit to use the current venv Python interpreter with TensorFlow installed.




